rently than normal people. I see a tree where you mights see a collection of lines, shapes, and shadows.\n\n- Stacey\n|\nI've always had an interest in design, and I have always loved creating things.\n\n- Jaime\n|\nCircumstances will change and things will be fine, just hold on a little more\n\n- Ishmael Beah, A Long Way Gone: Memoirs of a Boy Soldier\n|\nThe big bad monster wasn't green and hiding under the bed, it wore tasteless floral prints, bright scarlet lipstick and sat in the kitchen smoking and saying 'bollocks' alot.\n\n- Jo\n|\nEleanor should never have told them about Park's house, but she'd been dying to tell somebody. (This was how people ended up in jail after committing the perfect crime.)\n\n- Rainbow Rowell, Eleanor & Park\n|\nWe are saved by faith alone, but the faith that saves is never alone.\n\n- Martin\n|\nMusic, oh, how faint, how weak,Language fades before thy spell!Why should Feeling ever speak,When thou canst breathe her soul so well?\n\n- Thomas\n|\nPray, read and mediate on the Scripture. These spiritual deeds are the greatest acts to self-development\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!\n|\nPeople love you for what they want to see in you, not for what you are. That's a sad thing to learn.\n\n- Ava Dellaira, Love Letters to the Dead\n|\nThey all had darkened eyes, eyes that seemed to have a hunger behind them. Borne out of the private convulsions only secret passions can provoke.\n\n- Guy Mankowski, How I Left the National Grid: A post-punk novel\n|\nIf you suffer lingering doubts; if the consolation you cling to is ‘it will probably be okay,’ then run the other way because what you’re contemplating is not a good choice.\n\n- Richelle E. Goodrich, Slaying Dragons\n|\nHecuba had the mistaken notion, just like my poor mama, that all a girl had to do was to get married and all her problems were solved overnight.\n\n- Costas Taktsis, The Third Wedding\n|\nMistakes are painful when they happen, but years later a collection of mis